text: Don Francisco Javier Cornejo López (March 4, 1669, Ruesga, Cantabria - March 27, 1750, Madrid), also known as Don Francisco Javier Cornejo Vallejo, was a Spanish military commander of the Spanish navy. He participated in the successful Spanish expedition to Oran (1732). ==References== * Sánchez Doncel, Gregorio. Presencia de España en Orán 1509-1792. T.
